#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn148"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn148:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 148 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 148 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn148:0.2"
msgid "Chachakkasutta "
msgstr "Six By Six "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn148:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn148:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn148:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn148:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn148:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn148:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn148:2.1"
msgid "“dhammaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ, kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsessāmi, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Mendicants, I shall teach you the Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And I shall reveal a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure, namely, "

msgctxt "mn148:2.2"
msgid "cha chakkāni. "
msgstr "the six sets of six. "

msgctxt "mn148:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn148:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn148:2.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn148:3.1"
msgid "“Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbāni, cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbāni, cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā, cha phassakāyā veditabbā, cha vedanākāyā veditabbā, cha taṇhākāyā veditabbā. "
msgstr "“The six interior sense fields should be understood. The six exterior sense fields should be understood. The six classes of consciousness should be understood. The six classes of contact should be understood. The six classes of feeling should be understood. The six classes of craving should be understood. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc3
msgctxt "mn148:4.1"
msgid "‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:4.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn148:4.3"
msgid "Cakkhāyatanaṃ, sotāyatanaṃ, ghānāyatanaṃ, jivhāyatanaṃ, kāyāyatanaṃ, manāyatanaṃ. "
msgstr "There are the sense fields of the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind. "

msgctxt "mn148:4.4"
msgid "‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six interior sense fields should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:4.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

msgctxt "mn148:4.6"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ chakkaṃ. (1) "
msgstr "This is the first set of six. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, pts-vp-pli3.281, sc4
msgctxt "mn148:5.1"
msgid "‘Cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:5.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn148:5.3"
msgid "Rūpāyatanaṃ, saddāyatanaṃ, gandhāyatanaṃ, rasāyatanaṃ, phoṭṭhabbāyatanaṃ, dhammāyatanaṃ. "
msgstr "There are the sense fields of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts. "

msgctxt "mn148:5.4"
msgid "‘Cha bāhirāni āyatanāni veditabbānī’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six exterior sense fields should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:5.5"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

msgctxt "mn148:5.6"
msgid "Idaṃ dutiyaṃ chakkaṃ. (2) "
msgstr "This is the second set of six. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc5
msgctxt "mn148:6.1"
msgid "‘Cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:6.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn148:6.3"
msgid "Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.4"
msgid "sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.5"
msgid "ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.6"
msgid "jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.7"
msgid "kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.8"
msgid "manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.9"
msgid "‘Cha viññāṇakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of consciousness should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:6.10"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

msgctxt "mn148:6.11"
msgid "Idaṃ tatiyaṃ chakkaṃ. (3) "
msgstr "This is the third set of six. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc6
msgctxt "mn148:7.1"
msgid "‘Cha phassakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of contact should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:7.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn148:7.3"
msgid "Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso; "
msgstr "Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "mn148:7.4"
msgid "sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati sotaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso; "
msgstr "Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "mn148:7.5"
msgid "ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca uppajjati ghānaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso; "
msgstr "Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "mn148:7.6"
msgid "jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso; "
msgstr "Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "mn148:7.7"
msgid "kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca uppajjati kāyaviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso; "
msgstr "Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "mn148:7.8"
msgid "manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso. "
msgstr "Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact. "

msgctxt "mn148:7.9"
msgid "‘Cha phassakāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of contact should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:7.10"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

msgctxt "mn148:7.11"
msgid "Idaṃ catutthaṃ chakkaṃ. (4) "
msgstr "This is the fourth set of six. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, pts-vp-pli3.282, sc7
msgctxt "mn148:8.1"
msgid "‘Cha vedanākāyā veditabbā’ti—"
msgstr "‘The six classes of feeling should be understood.’ "

msgctxt "mn148:8.2"
msgid "iti kho panetaṃ vuttaṃ. Kiñcetaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ? "
msgstr "That’s what I said, but why did I say it? "

msgctxt "mn148:8.3"
msgid "Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso, phassapaccayā vedanā; "
msgstr "Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact. Contact is a condition for feeling. "

